main event: A civilian witness reported seeing a single unidentified object in West Carrollton, Ohio in 1969.
interesting points: The object appeared to change color, going from red to green.
The witness described the object as a 'candid color light appearing on top'.
The object was observed for an unspecified duration, with the witness still seeing it at 11:25.
The witness was a 'very reliable eye' and worked as a letter carrier for the post office.
The report includes a questionnaire form with detailed questions about the sighting, but the 'Brief Summary and Analysis' section is obscured and not legible.
